Practical10 
Aim: To study and implement security features and runtime permission handling in Android applications. 
Problem Statement: Develop an Android application that requests Camera permission at runtime. When the user clicks a button, the application should: 
Check whether the Camera permission is granted. If not granted, request the permission from the user. Display a message indicating whether the permission is granted or denied. 
The application should handle permission approval and denial properly. 
From Android 6.0 (Marshmallow) onwards, permissions like Camera, Location, etc. must be requested at runtime, not only in the Manifest. 
There are 3 main steps in runtime permission handling: 
Declare permission in AndroidManifest.xml 
Check permission using ContextCompat.checkSelfPermission() 
Request permission using ActivityCompat.requestPermissions() 
Handle result inside onRequestPermissionsResult() 
We will implement exactly this.

Project Setup 
Project Name: CameraPermissionApp 
Language: Java 
Template: Empty Views Activity 
Minimum SDK: API 23 or above 

1. AndroidManifest.xml 
Add Camera permission inside <manifest> but outside <application>. 
        <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.CAMERA"/> 
        
2. activity_main.xml 
          <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> 
          <LinearLayout 
          xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android" 
          android:layout_width="match_parent" 
          android:layout_height="match_parent" 
          android:gravity="center" 
          android:orientation="vertical"> 
          <Button 
          android:id="@+id/btnCamera" 
          android:layout_width="wrap_content" 
          android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
          android:text="Request Camera Permission"/> 
          </LinearLayout> 
          
3. MainActivity.java  
              package com.example.camerapermissionapp; 
              import android.Manifest; 
              import android.content.pm.PackageManager; 
              import android.os.Bundle; 
              import android.widget.Button; 
              import android.widget.Toast; 
              import androidx.annotation.NonNull; 
              import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity; 
              import androidx.core.app.ActivityCompat; 
              import androidx.core.content.ContextCompat; 
              public class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity { 
                  private static final int CAMERA_REQUEST_CODE = 100; 
                  Button btnCamera; 
                  @Override 
                  protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) { 
                      super.onCreate(savedInstanceState); 
                      setContentView(R.layout.activity_main); 
                      btnCamera = findViewById(R.id.btnCamera); 
                      btnCamera.setOnClickListener(v -> checkCameraPermission()); 
                  } 
                  private void checkCameraPermission() { 
                      // Step 1: Check if permission already granted 
                      if (ContextCompat.checkSelfPermission(this, 
                              Manifest.permission.CAMERA) == PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED) { 
               
                          Toast.makeText(this, 
                                  "Camera Permission Already Granted", 
                                  Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show(); 
                      } else { 
                          // Step 2: Request permission 
                          ActivityCompat.requestPermissions(this, 
                                  new String[]{Manifest.permission.CAMERA}, 
                                  CAMERA_REQUEST_CODE); 
                      } 
                  } 
                  // Step 3: Handle user response 
                  @Override 
                  public void onRequestPermissionsResult(int requestCode, 
                                                         @NonNull String[] permissions, 
                                                         @NonNull int[] grantResults) { 
                      super.onRequestPermissionsResult(requestCode, permissions, grantResults); 
                      if (requestCode == CAMERA_REQUEST_CODE) { 
                          if (grantResults.length > 0 
                                  && grantResults[0] == PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED) { 
                              Toast.makeText(this, 
                                      "Camera Permission Granted", 
                                      Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show(); 
                          } else { 
                              Toast.makeText(this, 
                                      "Camera Permission Denied", 
                                      Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show(); 
                          } 
                      } 
                  } 
              } 
              
What happens when button is clicked? 
checkCameraPermission() is called. 
App checks: 
If permission already granted → show message. 
If not granted → ask user for permission. 
1. System shows permission dialog. 
2. User selects Allow or Deny. 
3. onRequestPermissionsResult() receives result. 
4. Based on result → show proper message. 
How This Implements Security 
Runtime permission: 
• Prevents apps from accessing camera without user knowledge. 
• Gives user full control. 
• Improves privacy. 
• Prevents misuse of sensitive features.
